
An artificially-produced frog eye, the dark-trimmed dimple in the centre of the left piece, and a part of frog brain cells (right) in this undated picture released by the Japanese scientist, Mr. Makoto Asashima of the Graduate School of Arts and Science at Tokyo University. Mr. Asashima said on Monday his team had discovered how to artificially produce frog eyes and ears using the animal's own embryo cells, a process that he believes will be applicable in humans. The two pieces in the photo are about 2 millimetres in diameter.
- AP
